Package: xgecu-gui
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, udev
Description: Debian GUI for XGecu T48 / T56 / TL866II+ universal programmers
 A Qt6 desktop GUI for the XGecu T48 / T56 / TL866II+ universal device
 programmers, built on top of the open-source minipro library.
 .
 Features include programmer auto-detection, a searchable database of
 ~32 000 supported chips merged from minipro's XML and the Windows Xgpro
 list, a ZIF socket placement preview, separate Code and Data (EEPROM)
 tabs with an editable hex view (selection, fill, copy range, find with
 hex/ASCII/decimal modes, undo, red dirty-byte highlighting), and the full
 minipro programming pipeline: read, verify, blank check, detect chip ID,
 erase, write, auto-verify-after-write.
